geodemoTXT: Varieties and subdialects of Tsamakko are spoken in Ethiopia, ZZSouthern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples’ region: Omo area, lowlands west of Lake ChamoZZ.

termclusters.label: tsm-PronounIndependent
termclusters.note: Sa05t19;25 ::  Note also Table 22:Haplology in 1Pl dative pronoun:1Pl regular form is ʔine;cliticisation of =nnu gives *ʔine=nnu;reduction gives ʔi=nnu. Table 23 Syllabification of 1Sg,2SgM,and 2SgF dative pronouns:1sg *ʔee=nnu goes_to *ʔeen.nu goes_to ʔin.nu;2sg m *koo=nnu goes_to *koon.nu goes_to kun.nu;2sg f *kee=nnu goes_to *keen.nu goes_to kin.nu. Table 24:Syllabification of 1sg,2SgM,and 2SgF directive pronouns:1sg ʔee=ma goes_to ʔee.ma;2sg m koo=ma goes_to koo.ma;2sg f kee=ma goes_to kee.ma.

termclusters.label: tsm-Verbmorph-TenseSuffSets-
termclusters.note: Sa05t38-42 :: Sava2005,6.4.5,table 42. suffSet 5 = adjectival verbs denoting permanent states (color,size,permanent quality). Complete list,pp.149f. See Sava,pp.158-161 on category ‘sub’ (‘subordinate’ – here included as value of ‘pol’),occurring only with the future. ‘past’ and ‘nonPast’ occur only in the negative,and are formally related to the ‘imperf’ and ‘aorist’,respectively,of the affirmative.
